      "quotes_count": 0,
      "edited_at": null,
      "content": "<p>Sometimes it is useful to parameterize what comes before however, i.e. systemd-boot and systemd-stub. Since systemd v254 you could already configure the kernel command line via SMBIOS Type #11 vendor strings: that&#39;s what io.systemd.stub.kernel-cmdline-extra= and io.systemd.boot.kernel-cmdline-extra= are for. With v258 we are adding one more SMBIOS Type #11 vendor string: io.systemd.boot-entries.extra. It can carry one or more Boot Loader Spec Type #1 definitions of additional boot menu entries.</p>",
      "reblog": null,
